(110, 1, '2017-04-28 03:35:43', '2017-04-28 07:35:43', 'The Chicago Sky have signed Destiny Williams to a training camp contract. Williams, a 61 power forward/center, graduated from Baylor University where she won a National Championship during the 2011-2012 season. Williams received the Big 12 Conference Sixth Woman Award in 2013 and the Big 12 Championship All-Tournament Team Award in 2012 and 2013.\r\n\r\nWilliams played in the Spanish Womens Basketball League for Liga Femenina, where she averaged 18.3 points and13.4 rebounds and was named 2016-17 Most Valuable Player. Most recently, Williams joined the South Korean Womens Basketball League for Shinhan Bank S-Birds Anshan. She was named All-Korean WKBL 1st Team in 2017. Per team policy, contract terms were not disclosed.', 'Chicago Sky Sign Destiny Williams to Training Camp Contract', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '107-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-04-28 03:35:43', '2017-04-28 07:35:43', '', 107, 'http://wordpress.nba.com/dream/107-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
